Adekalu Bulls Baseball club emerged the winners of the maiden edition of the South West Five Baseball Tournament in Lagos Adekalu Bulls defeated Glorious Liberty Baseball Club of Ekiti in a highly contested final by 5 to 4 runs in 5 innings. All efforts by Glorious Liberty Chuckles Baseball to thwart Adekalu Bulls’ efforts were checked to maintain their runs. The spectators described the final encounter between Adekalu Bulls Baseball and Softball Club final with Glorious Liberty Chuckles Baseball club of Ekiti as worth watching without any doubt. After the mind-blowing final, the President of Adekalu Bulls Baseball and Softball Club of Oshodi, Engineer Tope Alabi said the final encounter of the five Baseball would be a talk of the moment in the Baseball community in the country.   Infantino seeks third term as FIFA president     Injured Ndidi to miss rest of season     Amuneke cancels trip for World Cup Draws   According to Alabi, the newly introduced Baseball five was organized to get the country involved in modern-day baseball and softball techniques and activities. “This new format is an eye-opener and we will leverage on it, it will improve Nigeria’s status in Baseball five” Said Alabi. Meanwhile the Public Relations Officer (PRO) of the Nigeria Baseball and Softball Association, Robert Anthony applauded the organizers of the South West Baseball for thinking outside the box to stage a tournament like this. Over 20 teams in a single round-robin took part in South West Baseball five and they are Effortswill Academy, Glorious Liberty Chuckles Baseball club, K.F Dodgers of Ikorodu, Badagry Angels and Adekalu Bulls Baseball and Softball Club, and a host of others.